[1] Russia -- Chelyabinsk
Date: Thu, 3 Nov 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ria Novosti, 3 Nov 2005 [edited]
<http://en.rian.ru/russia/20051103/41987222.html>


A new outbreak of bird flu was registered in the Chelyabinsk region
in Russia's Urals Federal District Thursday. The press service of the
Russian Agriculture Ministry said a laboratory analysis had confirmed
a diagnosis of avian flu. This brings the number of villages
officially experiencing an outbreak of the virus in Russia up to 13.

